# Environment variables for Render deployments
#
# This file is a convenience reference you can copy from when configuring each
# Render Web Service. Render does not read a project-level .env file — instead
# set these values in the Render dashboard for each service.
#
# Replace placeholders with the actual Render-provided service URLs or secrets.

# --- Common / global ---
NODE_ENV=production

# --- wallet-service (no required envs by default) ---
# WALLET_URL is the public URL for the wallet service. Example below is a sample
# Render URL you provided earlier; change it to the actual wallet service URL.
WALLET_URL=https://trying-sd-1.onrender.com

# --- game-service ---
# game-service calls the wallet service using WALLET_URL.
GAME_PORT=3000
WALLET_URL=${WALLET_URL}

# --- mock-frontend ---
# Frontend will connect to the game-service via WebSocket. Use wss:// for TLS.
MOCK_FRONTEND_PORT=8080
GAME_URL=ws://trying-sd-1.onrender.com
USER_ID=user-1

# --- Redis (if you create a managed Redis on Render) ---
# Render gives you a REDIS_URL value - copy it here when available.
REDIS_URL=redis://<render-redis-host>:6379

# Notes:
# - Copy the relevant values into each Render service's Environment section.
# - Do NOT commit real secrets to the repository. Use Render's dashboard secrets.
